<HEADLINE> 6 Killed, 13 Injured in Portugal Train Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, November 9 (Xinhua) -- At least six people were killed
today when two passenger trains crashed head-on in southern
Portugal Saturday, reports said.
</P>
<P>
13 other people were injured when the two trains collided near
Portimao, some 200 kilometers (125 miles) south of Lisbon.
</P>
<P>
Identities of the victims were not available but news reports
said the two train motormen were among the dead.
</P>
<P>
The trains were said to be carrying about 70 people. Portimao
is a popular holiday resort.
</P>
<P>
Reports said the likely cause of the accident was human
error. On the part of the line where the crash occurred, the
railway is single track with traffic flow controlled by signals.
</P>
</TEXT>
