<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading British Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, November 9 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading British newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
The Sunday Times:
</P>
<P>
-- Everybody of working age may be forced to take out their own
do-it-yourself welfare plan under radical proposals being drawn up
by the government to reform the welfare state.
</P>
<P>
Sunday Telegraph:
</P>
<P>
-- Britain is considering deploying Tornado jets in a joint
military strike with America against Iraqi bases, if Saddam
Hussein does not back down from his latest confrontation with
United Nations weapons inspectors.
</P>
<P>
