<DOCNO> XIE19971110.0005 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Resettlement in Three Gorges Area Supported </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YICHANG, November 9 (Xinhua) -- The State Planning Commission
will give all-round support to the resettlement of the people
affected by the construction of the gigantic Three Gorges Dam
Project.
</P>
<P>
The commission will help speed up economic growth, increase
investment and cooperation, prevent water from contamination and
carry out sustained development strategies in the Three Gorges
area.
</P>
<P>
Chen Yaobang, vice minister of the State Planning Commission,
made the remarks today at the State Council Three Gorges
Resettlement Working Conference.
</P>
<P>
Since 1993 the commission has made on-the-spot research in the
Three Gorges area and drew up a program for its economic
development. The program provides a scientific guideline for
economic growth, relocation of production facilities, and
resettlement of residents and national support for projects in the
area.
</P>
<P>
The commission has increased investment in the area'
agriculture, infrastructure construction and basic industrial
development. Since 1991 the commission has committed 800 million
yuan for the resettlement of residents and small-sized
irrigation and water conservation projects in the area.
</P>
<P>
More than 20 billion yuan will have been invested in
transportation, energy, raw materials and urban infrastructure
construction in the Three Gorges area. The completed projects
include the Three Gorges airport in Yichang and a new bridge over
the Yangtze River in Chongqing.
</P>
<P>
The commission also has attached importance to the improvement
of the environment and the protection of water quality in the
Three Gorges area. During recent years it has joined hands with
other departments in planting trees on the upper reaches of the
Yangtze and investing 500 million yuan to prevent
soil erosion in a 39,000-square-kilometer area.
</P>
<P>
The commission also has cooperated with other departments to
set up a committee in charge of overseas investment and
cooperation, which is expected to aid the resettlement
program. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
