<HEADLINE> Oman, Britain Sign Tank Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, November 9 (Xinhua) -- Oman today clinched a
military deal with Britain's Vickers Defense System Corporation on
purchasing 20 "Challenger 2" main battle tanks, the Oman News
Agency said.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was inked in the Omani capital Muscat today by
Omani Defense Minister Bader bin Saud bin Harib al Busaede, and
Vickers' representative Kris Wood Werk.
</P>
<P>
The news agency gave no details about the agreement, but
informed sources said that under the agreement, the Oman's royal
army is expected to get the tanks earlier next year.
</P>
<P>
It is Oman's second import order for the tanks manufactured by
Vickers.
</P>
<P>
In January, 1993, the tiny Gulf island state spent some 225
million dollars to buy from Vickers dozens of the "Challenge 2" as
the new generation of main battle tank for its army. 
</P>
</TEXT>
