<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Four Million Ethiopian Children Facing Various </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, November 9 (Xinhua) -- About four million
Ethiopian children, of whom 100,000 are street children, are
facing various types of problems, Ethiopia's monthly magazine
''Merewa''reported.
</P>
<P>
A study conducted by the United Nations Children's Fund in 25
Ethiopian towns shows that another 500,000 children, who have no
one to look after them, are on the brink of joining others on the
street, reported the Ethiopian News Agency today, quoting the
Amharic language magazine.
</P>
<P>
A protracted civil war, natural calamities, displacement
caused by man-made and natural disasters and the break of
families were cited by the magazine as the main causes of the
suffering of the children.
</P>
<P>
The study revealed that only 25,000 children are being catered
for in 106 chidlren centers in the country and out of the two
million disabled children, only 3,000 are getting social
services.
</P>
<P>
Another reason for the suffering of the chidlren, the magazine
said, is the abandonment of the traditional extended family
systems, especially in cities and towns, which traditionally
provided welfare to the elderly and children.
</P>
<P>
The magazine, which was published by the Ministry of
Information and Culture, stressed the need to carry out a
cultural rehabilitation to revive older traditions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
