<HEADLINE> Macao Trade Delegation Arrives in Mozambique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, November 9 (Xinhua) -- The Macao business and trade
delegation arrived here this afternoon to explore the possibility
of investment in the Portuguese-speaking African country.
</P>
<P>
Victor Pessoa from Macao's Economic Coordination Department,
and head of the 19-strong delegation, said at the airport that
the visit is aimed at establishing trade relations with
Mozambique.
</P>
<P>
According to Pessoa, there had been a close trade relationship
between Macao and Mozambique in the first half of 1970s. Later,
due to internal strife in Mozambique, trade volume was brought
down greatly. The current visit by the Macao delegation is to
renew bilateral trade ties.
</P>
<P>
What's more important, he added, is that Mozambique is now in
a period of economic rehabilitation and development, which offers
great prospects to foreign investors.
</P>
<P>
The trend of globalization has prompted Macao's enterprises to
increase their investment in southern China and other regions,
Pessoa noted.
</P>
<P>
He said that despite the small scale of Macao's economy, it
has the ability to invest in foreign countries. he expressed his
belief that Macao's entrepreneurs would make contributions to
Mozambican economy.
</P>
<P>
Pessoa said that the Macao delegation shows much interest in
textile, civil architecture and fishery and it will do its best
to work out trade and investment deals during the visit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
