to settle their differences on troops redeployment, Jewish
settlement, airport and seaport in Gaza, safe passage route
between Palestinian self-rule areas and other issues as agreed
upon at the Washington talks.
</P>
<P>
In order to break the impasse of the peace talks,
U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright is scheduled to hold
talks with Israeli Prime minister Benjamin Netanyahu in London
this Friday and with PNA Chairman Yasser Arafat in Geneva a day
later. 
</P>
