According to the city's Department of Public Works, a total of
150 tons of litter was cleared away from the streets. In his State
of the City address in October the mayor said that the "Great
Sweep" may pick up and cart off 300 tons of loose trash and people
may get into the habit of feeling responsible for their streets.
</P>
