<HEADLINE> Iraq Denies Ability to Produce Chemical Weapons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, November 9 (Xinhua) -- Iraq is unable to manufacture
chemical weapons, a spokesman of Iraq's Ministry of Culture and
Information said today.
</P>
<P>
He made the denial while commenting on a statement by Richard
Butler, chairman of the United Nations Special Commission (UNSCOM)
for dismantling Iraq's mass destructive weapons, Iraqi News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
Butler said recently that Iraq still had the capability to
produce items that could be used to manufacture chemical weapons
within days.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said Butler was "not accurate" in his statement
because he knew "quite well" that the UNSCOM had destroyed
everything that was directly related to chemical weapons.
</P>
<P>
The UNSCOM must verify that Iraq has eliminated chemical,
biological and nuclear weapons before the U.N. Security Council
could decide to lift economic sanctions imposed on Iraq since its
1990 invasion of Kuwait.
</P>
<P>
"We do not claim that he is unaware of the facts, but rather
say he is ignoring them," said the spokesman. 
</P>
