<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU, Albania Sign Memorandum on Customs Assistance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, November 10 (Xinhua) -- A memorandum of understanding
was signed here today by the European Union (EU) and Albania,
which is aimed at establishing a legal framework for the
activities of the Customs Assistance Mission set up by the EU in
Albania.
</P>
<P>
The Customs Assistance Mission was established as part of the
European Commission's request for support that the Albanian
government addressed to the international community following the
unrest in the country in 1997.
</P>
<P>
During the recent unrest in Albania, sparked off by the
collapse of pyramid savings schemes, the government lost control
of Albania border crossings, and the customs authorities were
unable to collect customs duties and taxes on imported goods.
</P>
<P>
The memorandum, signed by the EU Customs Commissioner Mario
Monti and Arben Malaj, minister of finance of Albania, notes that
one of the pre-conditions for international donor assistance to
Albania was that the government should take control of the border
crossings.
</P>
<P>
During the donors conference on Albania which was held in
Brussels on October 22, 1997, the participants noted that this
pre-condition had been met. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
