<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australians Win Second Day at OOCL Yachting Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 10 (Xinhua) -- Australians, who took the
top three places in the opening race on Sunday, continued their
triumphant advance by winning the top two spots on the second day
of the 1997 Oriental Overseas Container Line Ltd. (OOCL) Etchells
World Yachting Championships here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Australians Noel Drennan, winner of the opening race on Sunday,
and fellow countryman and America's Cup legend John Bertrand led
throughout the race today to sail to the finish first and second.
</P>
<P>
Briton Adam Goslin, who chased the two all the way by sailing
in 17 knots of wind through today's race, finished third.
</P>
<P>
Denmark's two-time Olympic champion Poul-Richard Hoj-Jensen,
fifth on Sunday, was fourth today.
</P>
<P>
Another Briton Barry Parkin was fifth and 1996 Olympic bronze
medalist and two-time Etchells world champion Colin Beashel came
out a surprisingly just sixth.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's Mark Thornburrow, fourth on Sunday, finished
eleventh.
</P>
<P>
The sailors are allowed to throw one out of the six races of
the eight-day world championships.
</P>
<P>
Competing in the world championships are thirty boats and 91
sailors from six countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
The eight-day OOCL World Championships close on November 15.
</P>
</TEXT>
