<HEADLINE> Beijing Hosts Meeting of Sino-Russian Friendship Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 10 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
and Russian President Boris Yeltsin sent congratulatory notes
marking the first meeting of the Sino-Russian Friendship Committee
for Peace and Development which was held today in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Jiang wrote that the development of the strategic and
cooperative Sino-Russian partnership oriented toward the 21st
century enjoys extensive social foundation in both China and
Russia, and that the idea of engaging in a long-term cooperation
is deeply rooted in the hearts of the two peoples.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that maintaining and developing the sound momentum
of bilateral relations is in the fundamental interests of the two
countries and their peoples.
</P>
<P>
Jiang pointed to the fact that both China and Russia are
neighbors and are both permanent members of the United Nations
Security Council. He said the two countries bear a common
responsibility for world peace and development.
</P>
<P>
Promoting peace and development is the unshirkable obligation
of statesmen, and also the lofty cause of the people in their
common efforts, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that he and President Yeltsin proposed the
establishment the committee which is designed to root the idea of
promoting Sino-Russian cooperation, maintaining peace and seeking
common development in the hearts of the two peoples.
</P>
<P>
The committee's work will inspire future generations to
continue the effort, said Jiang.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin said that the establishment of the committee was the
inevitable consequence of the development of the new Sino-Russian
relationship. He noted that the committee will enjoy a bright
future.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin pointed to the fact that older generations of leaders
from the two countries forged a profound and traditional
friendship, and that the two countries supported each other during
difficult periods. He noted that the two countries are linked by
the common goal of establishing a strategic cooperative
partnership based on equality and mutual trust, and oriented to
the 21st century, "I wish the committee great success in its
work," said Yeltsin.
</P>
<P>
Huang Yicheng, vice-chairman of the Financial and Economic
Committee of China's National People's Congress, and Volskiy
Arkadiy Ivanovich, chairman of the Russian Union of Industrialists
and Entrepreneurs, who serve as co-presidents of the committee,
expressed the conviction that the committee will be able to make
major contributions to the growth of mutual understanding and
cooperation between the two peoples.
</P>
<P>
Huang and Volskiy signed an agreement on the principles guiding
the committee's activities.
</P>
<P>
The committee, established in April of 1997, consists of
Chinese and Russian representatives from all walks of life. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
