<HEADLINE> Beijing Hosts Exhibition of Russian Treasures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 10 (Xinhua) -- A two-week exhibition of
treasures from the Russian National Treasury opened here today.
</P>
<P>
Two thirds of the items included in the largest exhibition of
Russian treasures outside that country have never before been
displayed in Russia.
</P>
<P>
Russian First Deputy Prime Minister Boris Nemtsov, who is
accompanying President Boris Yeltsin on his two-day state visit to
China, and Huang Hua, chief advisor to the China Association for
International Friendly Contact (CAIFC), attended the opening
ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The goals of the exhibition are to promote friendship
and cultural exchanges and mutual understanding between the
Chinese and Russian peoples, according to an association official.
</P>
<P>
The 1,690 items on display are normally housed in the
collection of the Gokhran of Russia. The items include a natural
gold nugget weighing 1,581.8 grams, a 46-kg gold ball fashioned in
1890, and several of the world's most precious medallions.
</P>
<P>
The noncommercial exhibition is jointly hosted by the CAIFC and
the Gokhran of Russia.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
