<HEADLINE> Beijing Hosts Economic and Trade Cooperation Seminar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 10 (Xinhua) -- A Cross-Straits and Hong Kong
Special Administration Region Economic and Trade Cooperation
Seminar opened today in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The two-day seminar is the third annual activity of its kind
sponsored by the All-China Federation of Industry and Commerce
(ACFIC), the Taiwan Chamber of Commerce and Industry, and the
Chinese Manufacturers Association of Hong Kong. The previous two
seminars were held in Beijing and Taipei.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 representatives from industrial and commercial
circles in China's inland areas, as well as their counterparts
from Taiwan and Hong Kong are attending the seminar which will
focus on topics such as scientific and technological development
and cooperation, past and future biological technology, and
economic and trade development and investment.
</P>
<P>
Discussions will focus on high technology, with special
emphasis on cooperation related to biological
technology. Participants will be encouraged to take full advantage
of the solid foundation of inland markets, as well as information
and funds from Taiwan and Hong Kong to accelerate the introduction
of technological achievements and improve their competitiveness in
overseas markets.
</P>
<P>
ACFIC Chairman Jing Shuping called on representatives from
industrial and commercial sectors in Taiwan and Hong Kong to grasp
opportunities to actively join in economic construction in inland
areas. He noted that the ultimate goal will be to achieve greater
results which benefit the people, and improve cross-Straits
economic development, as well as development in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Hsui Sheng-Fa, chairman of the Board of the Taiwan Chamber of
Commerce and Industry, and Fei-Shi Lin, vice-president of the
Chinese Manufacturers Association of Hong Kong, called for more
practical long-term cooperation with inland areas in order to
promote economic prosperity across the Straits and in Hong Kong.
</P>
</TEXT>
