<HEADLINE> Switzerland to Grant 3.41 Million Dollars to Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, November 10 (Xinhua) -- Switzerland will grant a
total of some 197.8 million rupees (about 3.41 million U.S.
dollars) to Nepal under two agreements the two countries signed
here today, Nepal's official RSS news agency said.
</P>
<P>
Nepali Prime Minister Surya Bahadur Thapa and visiting Swiss
President Arnold Koller were present at the signing ceremony of
the agreements.
</P>
<P>
Under the first accord, the government of Switzerland will
grant some 99.5 million rupees (about 1.72 million dollars) for
the construction and maintenance of 100 suspension bridges in
Nepal's hill districts.
</P>
<P>
Under the second agreement, about 98.3 million rupees (about
1.69 million dollars) will be provided for constructing some 485
suspension bridges in 52 districts of Nepal within four years.
</P>
<P>
Switzerland provides aid to Nepal mainly in the fields of
transport, human resource development, agriculture, forestry and
fisheries.  
