<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPPCC Chairman Meets German Parliamentarian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 10 (Xinhua) -- Mankind must carefully,
objectively and scientifically summarize the experience and
lessons of the 20th century, according to Li Ruihuan.
</P>
<P>
Li, chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), made the remark during
today's meeting with visiting German Parliamentarian Hans-Dietrich
Genscher.
</P>
<P>
Li expressed the hope that people throughout the world will
learn from useful experiences and make every effort to prevent the
reoccurrence of bad experiences.
</P>
<P>
"We are greatly concerned about what kind of a world we will
face in the 21st century," said Li. He added that in the past 100
years breakthroughs in economic development and the natural
sciences have be made while major achievements recorded in the
struggle for national liberation and independence.
</P>
<P>
Li said that mankind has witnessed many catastrophic events
during this century, including two world wars. However, historical
experiences have provided people with greater insight, according
to Li.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that the process of learning from history has
enabled experienced statesmen like Genscher to publicly exchange
views and "their views will be highly significant for
enlightening later generations," said Li.
</P>
<P>
Genscher, a former federal vice-chancellor and minister for
foreign affairs, echoed Li's sentiments. He said that worldwide
development and the future happiness of the mankind lie in
reaching correct conclusions from past misfortunes.
</P>
<P>
He described China as an important pillar in efforts to improve
the world.
</P>
<P>
Genscher is visiting China at the invitation of CPPCC
Vice-Chairman Wu Xueqian.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
