<HEADLINE> Promising Future for Beijing Cooperation with HK and Taiwan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 10 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese capital has a
promising future for wide-ranging economic cooperation with Taiwan
and Hong Kong, according to Mayor Jia Qinglin.
</P>
<P>
Jia made the remarks today during a meeting with visiting
delegations from Taiwan and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Jia warmly welcomed the delegations, led respectively by Hsui
Sheng-Fa, chairman of the Board of the Taiwan Chamber of Commerce
and Industry, and Fei-Shi Lin, vice-president of Chinese
Manufacturers Association of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Jia thanked members of the delegations for attending the
Cross-Straits and Hong Kong Special Administration Region Economic
and Trade Cooperation Seminar which opened today in Beijing. He
said their participation will promote economic exchange and
cooperation of China's inland areas with Taiwan and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing-Taiwan Economic Seminar held last year and this
year's Beijing-Hong Kong Economic Cooperation Seminar have greatly
enhanced economic and trade cooperation, said Jia.
</P>
<P>
He noted that Hong Kong is the leading overseas investor in
Beijing with total investments of 17.6 billion US dollars, while
Taiwan ranks third with investments of 2.4 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The city is attempting to keep pace with the modernization of
urban infrastructure by encouraging foreign investments in the
pharmaceutical, bio-engineering, electronics, information
processing sectors, as well as in other hi-tech industries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
