<HEADLINE> Senior Chinese Parliament Official Visits Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, November 10 (Xinhua) -- Chen Muhua, vice chairwoman
of the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC)
of China, arrived here this afternoon for a five-day official
goodwill visit to Nepal at the invitation of the Nepali
parliament.
</P>
<P>
Chen and her delegation were greeted by Nepali Upper House Vice
Chairman Chiranjibi Rijal and some parliament members.
</P>
<P>
In a written statement upon her arrival, Chen said the exchange
of visits by the heads of state of China and Nepal last year,
during which they decided upon the establishment of a 21st
century-oriented partnership of lasting friendship and good
neighborliness, has brought the Sino-Nepali friendly relations to
a new stage.
</P>
<P>
"This is my first visit to your country, and it is designed to
enhance exchanges and mutual understanding between our two peoples
as well as between the NPC and your parliament," Chen said.
</P>
<P>
She said she is convinced that with her visit, the existing
good-neighborly friendship and cooperation between the two
countries will enjoy continued development.
</P>
<P>
During her stay in Nepal, Chen will call on Nepali Prime
Minister Surya Bahadur Thapa, parliament leaders and King
Birendra.
</P>
<P>
Chen came to Nepal after attending the Golden Jubilee
celebrations of the independence of Pakistan as the special envoy
of the Chinese government.
</P>
<P>
She will also visit Sri Lanka and the Maldives at the
invitation of the parliaments of the two countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
