<HEADLINE> CPPCC Chairman Meets Indonesian Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 10 (Xinhua) -- Li Ruihuan, chairman of the
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC), met here today with a delegation from the
Supreme Advisory Council of Indonesia, led by Chairman Sudomo.
</P>
<P>
Li warmly welcomed the delegation and noted the Sino-Indonesian
relations are developing smoothly. He said the two countries share
either identical or similar views on major international issues.
</P>
<P>
Li cited constant exchange of visits between leaders of the two
sides, and noted the rapid development of bilateral economic and
trade relations. He said that he is glad to see the two countries
have continuously strengthened cooperation in wide-ranging
international and regional affairs related to human rights,
democracy and environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
Li noted that Indonesia has been adversely affected by the
financial turmoil in Southeast Asia and a forest fire, and
expressed China's concern about the great losses of Indonesia's
national economy and the sufferings of its people from the
continuing forest fires.
</P>
<P>
"We believe that the leadership of President Suharto will
enable the Indonesian government and people to overcome related
difficulties and will ensure that national economic development
resumes a healthy path", said Li.
</P>
<P>
He also noted that the CPPCC and Supreme Advisory Council of
Indonesia have strengthened cooperation and maintained a sound
relationship in recent years, and expressed his belief that
Sudomo's current visit to China will promote the development of
relations between the two organizations and enhance mutual
understanding between the two peoples.
</P>
<P>
Sudomo expressed appreciation of the great concern the Chinese
government and people have exhibited with regard to Indonesia's
financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
He said that Indonesia and China, two of the world's most
populous countries, face no major problems requiring urgent
solutions.
</P>
<P>
Sudomo conveyed President Suharto's greetings to Li and invited
him to Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
Li thanked Sudomo for the invitation and requested him to
convey his best wishes to Suharto.
</P>
<P>
CPPCC Vice-Chairwoman Qian Zhengying attended the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesian delegation is visiting China at the invitation
of the CPPCC. 
</P>
</TEXT>
