<HEADLINE> China's Top Legislator Meets Russian President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 10 (Xinhua) -- The fact that five summits
have been held in the six years since China and Russia reaffirmed
their relations demonstrates a good momentum in the development of
Sino-Russian ties.
</P>
<P>
Qiao Shi, Chairman of the Standing Committee of China's
National People's Congress (NPC), made the remark during a meeting
with visiting Russian President Boris Yeltsin in the Great Hall of
the People here today.
</P>
<P>
Extending a warm welcome to Yeltsin on his third state visit to
China, Qiao said that relations with Russia, China's biggest
neighbor, constitute a focus of China's foreign policy.
</P>
<P>
The development of Sino-Russian good-neighborly relations of
friendship and mutually beneficial cooperation enjoys an extensive
social basis in China, Qiao said, adding that both common people
and deputies to the National People's Congress are interested in
Russia and welcome the establishment of the Sino-Russia strategic
cooperative partnership.
</P>
<P>
Each time the NPC sessions examine agreements and discuss
relations between China and Russia, the deputies are "very active
and enthusiastic," he said.
</P>
<P>
Qiao recalled his visit to Russia in March 1996, when he saw
considerable improvement of market supply and urban construction
there. He voiced happiness with the improvement in the Russian
economy in the past year and more.
</P>
<P>
Describing Russia as a nation with a solid economic basis and
vast potentials, Qiao expressed the conviction that with arduous
efforts over a period of time, Russia is sure to score more
progress in the course of revitalization.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese top legislator noted that in recent years,
parliaments of the two countries have enjoyed active exchanges,
saying this is an important part of Sino-Russian relations.
</P>
<P>
Qiao stressed that the NPC is ready to work with the Russian
parliament to push for constant advancement of bilateral friendly
ties of cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin said he was very glad to meet Qiao, noting he had
wide-ranging talks with President Jiang Zemin earlier
today. "We're very satisfied with the development of Russia-China
relations," he said.
</P>
<P>
During his last visit to China in April 1996, he said, the two
sides signed a joint statement and more than 10 cooperation
agreements. In review of this, both sides are doing well in
implementing these documents, he said, adding the joint committee
of border demarcation has done a very good job in reaching
agreement on the eastern section of the Russia-China border.
</P>
<P>
On international issues, Yeltsin said that the two sides share
common positions on many international issues and cooperate well
in the UN affairs.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, the Russian president also briefed Qiao on
Russia's domestic circumstances.
</P>
<P>
Qiao asked Yeltsin to pass on his best regards to Yegor
Semeonovich Stroyev, Chairman of Russia's Federation Council, and
to Gennady Seleznev, Chairman of the State Duma.
</P>
<P>
Present at today's meeting were Liu Zhongli, chairman of the
Chinese government reception committee and Minister of Finance,
and Russian First Deputy Prime Minister Boris Nemtsov and Foreign
Minister Yevgeny M. Primakov.  
</P>
</TEXT>
