<HEADLINE> Heilongjiang Opens 25 Trade Ports to Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, November 10 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's Heilongjiang
Province has opened 25 Category-A trade ports to Russia, according
to Vice-Governor Wang Zongzhang.
</P>
<P>
Heilongjiang is home to 10 percent of the nation's
state-approved Category-A trade ports, ranking second only to
Guangzhou Province.
</P>
<P>
Heilongjiang has attempted to improve the overall capacity of
the trade ports by allocating over three billion yuan for
upgrading ports and related transportation facilities, including
highways, railways and airports providing links from the
Sino-Russian border to central cities in the province.
</P>
<P>
In addition to opening ports, the province has also extended
great effort to improve truck transport on ice-covered rivers.
</P>
<P>
The border between Heilongjiang Province and Russia stretches
3,045 km., or 70 percent of the total length of the Sino-Russian
border.
</P>
<P>
Since 1990, the import and export between the province and
Russia has topped nine billion US dollars since 1990, or about 66
percent of total Sino-Russian trade for the period. Some eight
million people pass through the ports on a daily basis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
