<DOCNO> XIE19971110.0080 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese, Russian Presidents on Bilateral Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 10 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
and his Russian counterpart Boris Yeltsin held a session with the
press shortly after their talks here today.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that in the talks the two sides exchanged views on
bilateral relations and major international issues of common
concern in an indepth manner, and reached consensus on a wide
range of matters.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, Jiang said, Sino-Russian relations have
enjoyed comprehensive and healthy development through concerted
efforts of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
"The joint statement between China and Russia signed just now
by President Yeltsin and me summarizes the treasurable experience
and important achievements in the sound development of bilateral
ties in the last six years." he said.
</P>
<P>
Quoting the Chinese saying "friendly neighbors are treasurable
to a country," Jiang stressed that the good-neighborly relations
between China and Russia are not only the choice of politicians of
the two countries, but a common desire of the two peoples.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin, who arrived here last night for a two-day state
visit. said that Russia-China ties have scored sound growth in
recent years.
</P>
<P>
The two heads of state have just concluded the fifth summit in
a candid, sincere, friendly and constructive atmosphere, which
demonstrate that mutual trust has been established between the two
countries and their leaders, Yeltsin said.
</P>
<P>
This, he added, is of great importance to the development of
the friendship between the two countries and the two peoples.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, speaking of the strategic cooperative partnership
between Russia and China, which is oriented to the 21st century,
said that the relationship features full equality, mutual trust
and long-term good-neighborliness.
</P>
<P>
Established with good study of historical experience in
Sino-Russian relations, the relationship is in the fundamental
interests of the two peoples and will benefit world peace and
stability, he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang reiterated that China pursues an independent foreign
policy of peace, and develops relations with other countries by
following the principle of non-alignment and not being directed
against any third nation.
</P>
<P>
As the national conditions, historical backgrounds and
geographical positions vary from one country to another, China's
relations with them do not follow the same pattern, Jiang
said. However, he added, the relations do share one point in
common, that is the aim to maintain world peace and promote common
development.
</P>
<P>
China and Russia, as each other's largest neighboring nation
and permanent members of the United Nations Security Council,
shoulder a special responsibility for world peace and development,
Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang expressed satisfaction with the progress made in the
fruitful cooperation of the two countries on many important
issues, saying that the Chinese side is ready to work with the
Russian side to further enrich the existing partnership. 
</P>
</TEXT>
