<HEADLINE> Tung Elected to Head Presidium of HK NPC Deputies Election Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 10 (Xinhua) -- Tung Chee Hwa, Chief
Executive of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR),
was elected today Executive Chairman of the Presidium of the
Conference for Electing Deputies of the HKSAR to China's Ninth
National People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
Tung was chosen as the executive chairman at the first meeting
of the 11-member presidium this afternoon, Lee Cho-jat, spokesman
for the presidium, announced at a press briefing after the
presidium meeting.
</P>
<P>
Tung's duty as the executive chairman is to preside over
meetings of the presidium, Lee said.
</P>
<P>
At the press briefing, Tung told reporters that members of the
presidium had discussed a draft of the detailed method for
electing the HKSAR deputies to the Ninth NPC.
</P>
<P>
The draft detailed method agreed among the presidium members
will be submitted to the plenary session of the 424-member
Election Conference for further discussion in eight groups, Tung
said.
</P>
<P>
Tung said that the election of NPC deputies in HK is very
important because the NPC is China's supreme organ of state power.
</P>
<P>
The 36 deputies of the HKSAR will represent Hong Kong to
participate in the discussion of major state issues, Tung said,
adding that the Election Conference will work hard to choose the
right representatives.
</P>
<P>
The presidium had been elected by members of the Election
Conference at its first session this morning.
</P>
<P>
The presidium will preside over the Election Conference, work
out the Detailed Election Method and provide services for the
election.  
</P>
</TEXT>
