<HEADLINE> Northeast China Province Strengthens Ties with Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, November 10 (Xinhua) -- Heilongjiang Province in
northeast China has strengthened political, economic,
technological and cultural relations with Russia in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Provincial officials and their Russian counterparts have
conducted frequent exchanges since 1989.
</P>
<P>
Heilongjiang has also signed friendship agreements with
Armu and Khabarovskiy Kray of Russia.
</P>
<P>
Border trade between Heilongjiang and Russia has developed
rapidly since 1982. The province's trade volume with Russia in
l993 hit 2.06 billion U.S. dollars, or approximately 33 percent of
the Sino-Russian trade during the period.
</P>
<P>
Despite decreasing border trade between 1994-1996, the trade
volume for the first nine months of this year hit 690 million
U.S. dollars, up 96.4 percent on the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Russia is Heilongjiang's largest source of tourists, with some
80 percent of foreign tourists visiting the province coming from
the world's largest country.
</P>
<P>
Heilongjiang is also conducting fruitful cooperation with
Russia in the realm of agriculture, power generation,
machine-building and high technology. Some 2,000 teachers,
scholars and students from Heilongjiang and Russia have
participated in education exchang e programs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
