<HEADLINE> Palestinian Students Demonstrated in Bethlehem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, November 10 (Xinhua) -- Over one thousand Students
of Bethlehem University went to the streets today to
show their solidarity with Palestinian prisoner Ataf Alayan.
</P>
<P>
Shouting anti-Israeli slogans, the students marched from the
university campus to the center of the city of Bethlehem to demand
the release of Alayan, who is on a hunger strike in Israeli jail.
</P>
<P>
For fear that the situation might run out of control, Israeli
security forces and police fired tear gas into the crowd, forcing
the students to disperse.
</P>
<P>
Alayan was re-arrested by the Israeli police about three weeks
ago after being released from Israeli prison under the Oslo
Agreement signed between Israel and the Palestinian National
Authority (PNA).
</P>
<P>
Shortly after her arrest, she went on a hunger strike to
protest against the arrest and the her placement of
administrative detention without charge by Israel.
</P>
<P>
Her health is continuing to deteriorate due to the hunger
strike, causing worries among the Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
Echoing a call by the Palestinian prisoners organization, about
800 Palestinian prisoners staged a one-day hunger strike today in
various Israeli prisons to show their solidarity with Alayan.
</P>
<P>
Islamic Jihad Movement of Palestine issued a statement in Gaza
Strip on Sunday holding Israel full responsibility for the life
of Alayan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
