<HEADLINE> Heilongjiang University Promotes Sino-Russian Exchanges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, November 10 (Xinhua) -- Heilongjiang University in
Harbin, capital of northeast China's Heilongjiang Province, serves
a friendly bridge between Chinese and Russian citizens.
</P>
<P>
The university has attached great importance to research on
Russia. The university has also attempted to promote mutual
understanding by establishing the Russian Issue Research Center to
study language, philosophy, history, politics and economy of
Russia.
</P>
<P>
The university has established friendly cooperative ties with a
number of Russian universities, including the Pushkin Language
College, and was the first university in China to accept Russian
students. Some 20 Russian students study Chinese and the history
of China at the university each year.
</P>
<P>
Heilongjiang University, the only comprehensive university in
the province, has graduated about 7,000 students majoring in
Russian since the 1940s. 
