<HEADLINE> Chinese, Russian Foreign Ministers Meet in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 10 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier and
Foreign Minister Qian Qichen met with Russian Foreign Minister
Yevgeny Primakov here today.
</P>
<P>
Primakov is accompanying Russian President Boris Yeltsin on his
current state visit to China.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting at Zhongnanhai, the headquarters of the
central government, Qian said the current Sino-Russian Summit will
have a positive impact on international relations, especially
relations between large countries. He said the Fifth Joint
Communique signed by the two sides earnestly summarizes the
results and experience of the smooth development of bilateral
relations over the past six years. Qian noted that Yeltsin's
current visit will be highly beneficial for maintaining the
excellent momentum of the long-term stable and healthy development
of bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Primakov said the two state leaders engaged in friendly dialog
based on trust during their fifth summit. He noted that Yeltsin's
visit will achieve success and will promote the comprehensive
development of the strategic cooperative partnership between the
two nations.
</P>
<P>
Qian said that China is highly satisfied with the good
cooperation between the two countries on political issues.
</P>
<P>
The foreign ministers expressed the hope that the two sides
will further expand negotiations and cooperation in the realm of
international affairs.
</P>
<P>
They also exchanged in-depth views on the current international
situation.
</P>
<P>
Qian and Primakov demanded that Iraq immediately resume
cooperation with the United Nations and comprehensively and
literally implement all relevant UN Security Council resolutions.
</P>
<P>
They agreed that the Security Council should listen to the
opinions of both the UN Special Commission (UNSCOM) and Iraq in
order to reach a just and rational conclusion on the progress of
inspections.
</P>
<P>
The foreign ministers called for all concerned parties to adopt
an attitude of restraint and avoid any escalation of
contradictions, especially in terms of military conflict.
</P>
<P>
They said China and Russia are fully prepared to participate in
constructive efforts carried out by the Security Council.
</P>
<P>
Primakov briefed Qian on his recent trip to the Middle
East. The foreign ministers exchanged views on the Middle East
issue and noted they will continue to promote the peace process in
the region.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
