<HEADLINE> Mozambique Spots Unidentified Ships, Copters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, November 10 (Xinhua) -- The unidentified ships and
helicopters spotted along the coast of northern Mozambique's Cabo
Delgado Province is very worrisome, a high-ranking officer said
here today.
</P>
<P>
Raimundo Macie, police commissioner of the province was quoted
by the local daily Naticias as saying that the ships and
helicopters might be involved in robbery and drug trafficking.
</P>
<P>
This is the second time the provincial government revealed
such incidents in a month. Earlier on October 10, the
commissioner of Palma county said that within a period of four
weeks, ships and helicopters had been seen popping up and off
along the coast line of the county.
</P>
<P>
Macie said that the criminal rate in the province had
increased by 14 percent from January to October with 2,414 cases
recorded, adding that smuggling and drug trafficking are out of
control in the province for the special geological position and
the lack of supervision measures.
</P>
<P>
Over 590 illegal tree felling cases, 304 of whom were made by
foreigners, have also been recorded from January to October in
the province. 
</P>
