<HEADLINE> Chinese, Russian Presidents Hold Talks (5) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Yeltsin offered his congratulations on the smooth return of
Hong Kong to China and the successful convocation of the 15th
National Congress of the Communist Party of China. He also
expressed the hope that China will record new progress in its
modernization drive under the guidance of the spirit of the party
congress. "Russia hopes to see a prosperous and strong China,"
said Yeltsin.
</P>
<P>
Jiang expressed sincere appreciation for Yeltsin's
congratulatory words and best wishes. China and Russia, two great
neighboring countries which share a long border, have an important
positive role to play in safeguarding the regional and world peace
and stability as they gain ever greater prosperity, wealth and
strength, said Jiang.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese President briefed Yeltsin on his recent state visit
to the United States. Jiang addressed the international situation
by noting that China stands firm in its belief that a country
should have the final say in its own affairs, and world affairs
should be decided upon by all countries.
</P>
<P>
Great powers have a major responsibility for safeguarding world
peace and promoting international development, and should
therefore abandon a Cold War mentality, respect the reality of a
diversified world, conform to the trend of world
multipolarization, and establish cooperative relations based on
mutual respect, equality and trust, said Jiang.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said China will continue to adhere to Deng Xiaoping's
thoughts on foreign affairs, unswervingly uphold an independent
foreign policy of peace, actively develop friendly cooperative
ties with countries throughout the world, and work jointly to
create a new century featuring world peace and prosperity.
</P>
</TEXT>
