<HEADLINE> Huge Bridge in South China Completed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANTOU, November 10 (Xinhua) -- A 917-meter highway bridge has
been built over the Xinjin River of Shantou, a special economic
zone in south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
The two-way, four-lane bridge was jointly built by the
Guangdong Provincial Expressway Company and the Shantou City
Expressway Company at a total cost of more than 57 million
yuan. It is 24.5 meters wide.
</P>
<P>
The bridge connects with the Shenzhen-Shantou expressway, the
Shantou Gulf Bridge, and the No. 324 national highway. It will
also be part of the soon-to-be-built Shantou-Chaozhou-Fenshuiguan
expressway.
</P>
<P>
Officials note that the effort will accelerate the construction
of the local superhighway network and improve transportation
conditions in eastern Guangdong Province. 
</P>
