<HEADLINE> Premier Li Peng Meets President Yeltsin (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 10 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng and
his wife Zhu Lin had a cordial and friendly meeting today with
Russian President Boris Yeltsin and his wife Naina at the
Diaoyutai State Guesthouse.
</P>
<P>
Li expressed his belief that Yeltsin's state visit will further
advance the overall development of the strategic cooperative
partnership between China and Russia.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Premier warmly welcomed Yeltsin to China and
expressed his delight with seeing the Russian President once again
within only one year.
</P>
<P>
The international situation and relationships are experiencing
intensive change, with an acceleration in the positive and
irreversible trend towards a multipolar world. Large countries
should follow the trend by establishing healthy and stable
cooperative relationships on the basis of mutual respect,
equality, mutual interests and the spirit of seeking common ground
while reserving differences, said Li.
</P>
<P>
Li stressed that this will be essential for guaranteeing peace
and stability in the 21st century, and noted the Sino-Russian
relationship is proceeding healthily and steadily towards the new
century.
</P>
<P>
Li said this morning's talks between President Jiang Zemin and
President Yeltsin were highly fruitful and reached agreement in
extensive fields which will be highly significant for promoting
the further development of Sino-Russian relations.
</P>
<P>
He reaffirmed that China treasures the great achievements made
in bilateral relations, and is ready to join with Russia to create
a brighter future which will benefit the peoples of the two
countries and promote world peace and development.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin noted his delight in visiting China for a third time,
and expressed great satisfaction with today's talks with President
Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin noted that he and Jiang not only discussed politics,
economics and cooperation for large projects, but also issued an
important statement concerning a survey of the eastern section of
the Sino-Russian border, and signed a highly significant joint
statement.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin said his visit will without doubt be fruitful and will
have far-reaching significance.
</P>
<P>
Li pointed to his visit to Russia last December, and noted that
the two countries established a mechanism ensuring regular
meetings between the Chinese Premier and Russian Prime Minister.
</P>
<P>
Premier Li and Russian Prime Minister Chernomyrdin held their
second meeting during the latter's visit to China in June this
year. Respective committees from the two countries worked actively
on many cooperative projects and tabled numerous suggestions, said
Li, adding that the meeting mechanism will play an even more
positive role in strengthening future relations between the two
countries.
</P>
