<HEADLINE> TV Cameras to be Installed in Jo'burg City Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, November 10 (Xinhua) -- Closed-circuit
television cameras will be installed in Johannesburg's city
center to monitor security in the downtown streets, a municipal
official said at the weekend.
</P>
<P>
The cameras are expected to be in place by March next year,
once the manufacturer has been appointed and all the logistics
worked out, Central Johannesburg Partnership spokesman Franco
Andreone said.
</P>
<P>
He said research was still being done on how the system would
operate and where the cameras would be installed.
</P>
<P>
The cameras were likely to be placed on the fringes of the
city center in an effort to prevent crime moving to adjacent
areas, according to informed sources.
</P>
<P>
Johannesburg, a well-known trade center in South Africa, has
long been troubled with increasing crimes. 
</P>
