<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lithium Salt, New Treatment for Schizophrenia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, November 10 (Xinhua) -- Doctors at a mental hospital in
northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region have discovered
that lithium salt is an effective treatment for schizophrenia.
</P>
<P>
Psychiatry has long held that lithium salt can curb the
symptoms of mania, characterized by excessive excitement and
hallucinations, but not schizophrenia, or "split personality."
</P>
<P>
However, researchers at a psychiatric hospital in Xinjiang have
determined that lithium salt can alleviate symptoms of
schizophrenia.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Niu Peizhi from the psychiatric hospital in Xinjiang, tried
the lithium salt therapy on eight patients with schizophrenia and
discovered that their conditions improved in six to eight days.
They said the success rate of the lithium salt therapy could reach
98 percent.
</P>
<P>
A paper on the new therapy has been listed on the Internet by
Colby Information Center of Science and Culture of the United
States.
</P>
<P>
Chinese experts hold that mania and schizophrenia are basically
two forms of the same mental disease, though the clinical
manifestations vary. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
