government has full faith in the vast potential and mutual
benefits offered in the field. He said the two countries will
extend great effort to realize their goal of an annual trade
volume of 20 billion US dollars by year 2000.
</P>
<P>
Li expressed hope that both sides will work hard to carry out
cooperative projects, expand cooperation to fields other than
medium- to large-scale projects, and diversify patterns of
cooperation. He said the two sides will further develop local
economic and trade cooperation, especially border trade
cooperation, and will continue to promote strong ties between
Chinese and Russian companies and enterprises, while at the same
time encouraging mutual investments and the establishment of joint
ventures.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin expressed hope that the two sides will strengthen
economic and trade cooperation and fully tap the vast potential
for Sino-Russian economic and trade relations. He noted that
during his current visit relevant committees from the two
governments have conducted excellent work, making the visit even
more fruitful.
</P>
<P>
Premier Li Peng and his wife Zhu Lin hosted a banquet for
President Yeltsin and his wife Naina following the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The long list of dignitaries atteding the meeting and banquet
included Chinese Vice-Premier Li Lanqing, chairman of Chinese
Government Reception Committee and Minister of Finance Liu
Zhongli, Chinese Ambassador to Russia Li Fenglin, Russian First
Deputy Prime Minister Boris Nemtsov, Russian Foreign Minister
Yevgeny M. Primakov, Russian Ambassador to China Igor A. Rogachev,
and a number of other senior Chinese and Russian officials.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
