<DOCNO> XIE19971110.0132 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Karachi Jinnah Bridge Opens to Traffic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KARACHI, November 10 (Xinhua) -- The spectacular Jinnah Bridge
in this southern port city of Pakistan, a cooperation project
between Pakistan and China, was opened to traffic today.
</P>
<P>
The bridge was inaugurated by Pakistani Communication Minister
Muhammad Azam Hoti and visiting Chinese Special Envoy Chen Muhua,
who is also vice chairman of the Standing Committee of the
National People's Congress of China.
</P>
<P>
The ceremony was also attended by Sindh Chief Minister Liaquat
Ali Jatoi, State Minister for Water and Power Haleem Siddiqi,
members of the visiting Chinese delegation led by Chen and people
from Pakistan's communications sector.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the ceremony, Hoti said Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif
has issued instructions for rehabilitating Pakistan's existing
infrastructure and modernizing as well as expanding Pakistan's
port handling capacity to meet the challenges of the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
The Jinnah Bridge provides a vital link between the Karachi
port and the rest of the country. The project aims to provide a
safe and rapid integrated transportation system between the Port
of Karachi and the road network serving the hinterland of the
country, through the national highway system.
</P>
<P>
Chen, who came here from Lahore Sunday especially for the
inauguration of the bridge, said the bridge will serve as a symbol
of close and everlasting bond of friendship between the people of
Pakistan and China.
</P>
<P>
The bridge is the result of economic cooperation between the
two countries, she said.
</P>
<P>
This bridge, she said, will help improve the urban transport of
this city which has tremendously contributed to the national
economy and living standards of the people.
</P>
<P>
She added that Pakistan has made great strides during the last
50 years and will make more in the next 50 years.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan and China enjoy fraternal and close friendship and
cooperation, Chen said, adding that Pakistan has always supported
China at international forums for which the Chinese people are
greatly indebted.
</P>
<P>
After their speeches, Hoti and Chen unveiled the plaque
marking the inauguration of the bridge.  
</P>
</TEXT>
