<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HKMA Describes HK Banking System as "Strong" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 10 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Monetary
Authority (HKMA) denied today that certain local banks are
experiencing financial difficulties, saying the banking system
remains "strong" in the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region.
</P>
<P>
"The banking system in Hong Kong is strong and highly
capitalized" and "profits for local banks in the first nine months
 of this year compared well with those in the previous year," The
HKMA said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
All this provides a cushion for these banks to cope with the
current financial challenge, it added.
</P>
<P>
Denouncing rumors that some banks here are facing financial
difficulties, the statement said, "The HKMA has been monitoring
the situation closely and considers that these rumors are without
foundation."
</P>
<P>
Since late October, the stock market here has seen ups and
downs because of a speculative attack following the financial
turmoil in Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
"As the International Monetary Fund recently concluded after an
 assessment of the (Hong Kong) economy," the HKMA said in the
statement, "the strength of the banking system in Hong Kong means
that 'it will be able to withstand the effects of the recent
financial market volatility'."  
</P>
</TEXT>
