<HEADLINE> Share Prices Drift Lower on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, November 10 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continued to
drift lower on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times
Industrials Index declined by another 7.56 points to close at
1663.69 today.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said share prices were dragged down by a weaker finish
on Wall Street last Friday and fears of currency uncertainties.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume shrank further to 91.34 million units,
valued at 224.11 million Singapore dollars (about 143.66 million
U.S. dollars). Declines overwhelmed advances by 285 to 50 while
276 other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Land was the most actively traded counter as it
registered a turnover of 5.22 million units. It was followed by
Rekapac which had 5.12 million shares traded. DBS (Development
Bank of Singapore) Land saw 3.22 million of its shares changed
hands.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) led the gainers of the day
as it rose by 30 cents to finish at 14.1 Singapore dollars.
Sembawang Corporation and the United Overseas Bank (UOB) increased
by 20 cents each to end at 5.3 and 7.7 Singapore dollars
respectively. BAT picked up by 16 cents to close at 4.8 Singapore
dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, SPH Foreign was the biggest loser as it
declined by 3.3 dollars to end at 20.1 Singapore dollars. Bukit
Sembawang, the Singapore Airlines and the Uniphoenix lost 60 cents
each to close at 13.1, 11.5 and 6 Singapore dollars respectively.
Elec fell by 55 cents to finish at 7.2 U.S. dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
