<HEADLINE> Chinese, Russian Presidents Meet Sino-Russian Committee Members </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 10 (Xinhua)-- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
and visiting Russian President Boris Yeltsin met today in the
Great Hall of the People with members of the Sino-Russian
Committee for Friendship, Peace and Development.
</P>
<P>
Jiang and Yeltsin encouraged members of the newly-established
organization to work hard to contribute to the common development
and prosperity of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
"The goal for establishing the committee, jointly advocated by
President Yeltsin and myself, is to enhance mutual understanding
and the traditional friendship between the Chinese and Russian
people, and promoting greater cooperation between the two
countries in various fields," said Jiang.
</P>
<P>
He expressed hope that members of the committee will conduct
diversified forms of activities in order to contribute their share
to the common development and common prosperity of the two
countries. Jiang also wished the committee complete success in its
future work.
</P>
<P>
The committee convened its first meeting this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
President Yeltsin noted that Russia and China are friendly
neighbors engaged in mutually beneficial cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He said that leaders of the two countries have established
friendly ties, and pointed to the fact the committee offers broad
prospects for conducting various activities which will promote the
overall advancement of friendly bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
President Yeltsin also wished the committee complete
success. enditem
