<HEADLINE> French FM Meets with Iraqi Vice Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, November 10 (Xinhua) -- French Foreign Minister Hubert
Vedrine told Iraqi Vice Prime Minister Tarik Aziz here Sunday
evening that the measures taken by Iraq against the United Nations
mission on disarmament (UNSCOM) is "unacceptable".
</P>
<P>
Aziz was in Paris Sunday evening for a "technical stopover"
before flying to New York where the United Nations Security
Council will hold a meeting today on the confrontation between
Iraq and the UNSCOM.
</P>
<P>
French Foreign Ministry said in a communique this morning that
Vedrine "appealed to Iraq to take back these measures and abstain
from any act of the nature to block the activity of the special
commission."
</P>
<P>
Iraq once again blocked American arms inspectors of the UNSCOM
from carrying out their work on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
However, a U.S. U2 spy plane today completed its flight over
Iraq today without accident, despite Baghdad has threatened to
shoot down the plane. 
</P>
