<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese, Russian Presidents Hold Talks (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Yeltsin expressed his complete agreement with Jiang's views,
noting that China and Russia have established a strategic
cooperative partnership geared to the 21st century, a partership
which is based on trust and friendship, has concrete political and
economic contents and enjoys personal care and nurturing from top
leaders of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
There exist no questions between China and Russia, and this
meeting would continue to push ahead the relations between the two
countries, Yeltsin said.
</P>
<P>
The two heads of state announced officially that the
demarcation of the eastern section of the border between China and
Russia had been completed.
</P>
<P>
That is a matter of great significance for Sino-Russian
relations, Jiang said, noting that the two countries have signed
two border agreements, and signed some important documents on
confidence-building and disarmament along the border areas between
five countries.
</P>
<P>
The reaching of these agreements, including the demarcation of
borders, is a successful example for settling questions left over
by history through equal consultation, mutual understanding and
accommodation, and in a fair and reasonable way, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
The agreements are a powerful guarantee for the lasting peace,
tranquillity, development and prosperity in the border areas of
the two countries, he said.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin said that the two countries have settled the question
which had remain unsolved for decades, which is an embodiment of
friendly relations and cooperation between the two countries. It
accords with the fundamental interests of the two peoples for
China and Russia to have a peaceful, tranquil border, he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
