<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Egyptian Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, November 10 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Egyptian newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
Al-Ahram:
</P>
<P>
-- It has been confirmed that in a step to improve relations
between Egyptian and Sudanese government, Sudan will return to
Egypt all Egyptian properties confiscated by Sudan over the past
years.
</P>
<P>
Al-Akhbar:
</P>
<P>
-- President of Investment and Free Trade Zone Organization
Ibrahim Fawzi said Egypt's medical and pharmaceutical companies'
profits increased to 349 million Egyptian pounds (102 million
U.S. dollars) in 1995 from 69 million pounds (20 million dollars)
in 1991.
</P>
<P>
Al-Gomhuria:
</P>
<P>
-- Jordanian Crown Prince Hassan Ibn Talal met in Amman Sunday
with Israeli National Infrastructure Minister Ariel Sharon to
discuss bilateral relations and the pursuit of the implementation
of the Jordanian-Israeli peace treaty, signed in 1994.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian Gazette:
</P>
<P>
-- Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa Sunday warned that the
Middle East peace process has reached the stage of political
crisis because of current intransigent policies of the Israeli
government. 
</P>
