<HEADLINE> Chinese, Russian Presidents Hold Talks (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jiang Zemin noted satisfactorily that there has been a clear
orientation for developing China-Russia relations. That is "we
have established a strategic cooperative partnership geared to the
21st century and based on equality and trust."
</P>
<P>
He added that the two countries' relations have enjoyed a solid
political foundation, too. Through various joint statements and
other documents, the two sides have committed themselves to
strictly observing the principles of mutual respect, equality and
trust, mutually beneficial cooperation and common development.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have had an effective guarantee mechanism,
the Chinese president went on. That is a regular meeting system
involving heads of state, premiers and foreign ministers of the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
With the establishment and operation of the Sino-Russian
Committee for Friendship, Peace and Development, the friendship
and mutual understanding between the people of various walks of
life of the two countries will be strengthened, and the social
foundation for Sino-Russian friendly relations and cooperation
will be further deepened, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
"All this has convinced us to believe that there will be very
broad prospects for developing Sino-Russian relations," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
"That will not only further benefit the two peoples, but also
exert greater and positive influence on the sound development of
the international situation and international relations," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese side is willing to make concerted efforts with the
Russian side in pushing forward in an all-round way the strategic
cooperative partership to the next century, Jiang said.
</P>
</TEXT>
