<HEADLINE> Chinese, Russian Presidents Hold Talks (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 10 (Xinhua) -- In their talks today, both
Chinese and Russian presidents expressed the common view that
China-Russia relations have achieved fruitful results over the
past six years and a lot of precious experience has been
accumulated.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin and visiting Russian President
Boris Yeltsin held cordial and friendly talks at the Great Hall of
the People here this morning.
</P>
<P>
Jiang extended warm welcome to the Russian president for his
third visit to China, and expressed gladness to have the fifth
China-Russia summit.
</P>
<P>
"You are an old friend of ours, and I feel very pleased in each
meeting which is full of cordiality," Jiang Zemin said.
</P>
<P>
The two presidents said that facts have shown that it entirely
accords with the fundamental interests and aspirations of the two
peoples for China and Russia to establish a strategic cooperative
partnership geared to the 21st century, a partnership which is
featured by good-neighborliness, cooperation based on equality,
joint development, non-alignment, non-confrontation, and not being
directed against a third country.
</P>
<P>
Such partnership is also conducive to regional and global peace
and stability, they agreed.
</P>
