<HEADLINE> Eastern City Takes to High-Tech Industries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, November 10 (Xinhua) -- High-tech industries, including
electronics and chemicals, have replaced traditional ones such as
light industry and textiles in Suzhou city in east China's Jiangsu
Province.
</P>
<P>
These new key industries generate more than half of the total
output of the city.
</P>
<P>
The Suzhou New District and the Suzhou Industrial Park, where
many high-tech firms are located, have contributed to more than
one-third of the city's total industrial output.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, high-tech and foreign-funded
enterprises have also replaced foreign trade companies as the
largest exporters in the city. 
</P>
