<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Heilongjiang's Border Trade with Russia Prospers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, November 10 (Xinhua) -- The total volume of border
trade between northeast China's Heilongjiang Province and Russia
has topped nine billion US dollars in the last decade, according
to the local Chinese trade adminsitration statistics.
</P>
<P>
The Heilongjiang Provincial Border Trade Administration said
the volume of border trade between the province and Russia from
January to October is twice that of the same period in last year.
</P>
<P>
Trade between the two sides was formerly done by simple
bartering, but now has shifted to include cash trade, economic and
technical cooperation and invited investment.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government, facing the slump in Sino-Russian
border trade since 1993, has taken counteractive measures, such as
setting up a light industry products and agro-products processing
base on the border port, quality control checks on the exported
goods, and offering special training to the managers of those
companies engaged in border-trade.
</P>
<P>
These practices have helped the Sino-Russian border trade to
rebound.
</P>
<P>
The amount of border trade goods has grown from several hundred
to nearly 20,000 varieties, and the quality of the products has
improved, according to Ji Qingfu, head of the Heilongjiang
Provincial Border Trade Administration.
</P>
<P>
The economic structures of China and Russia are
complementary. Russia has a great demand for China's light
industry products, such as textiles, household appliances and
food, while China needs Russia's raw materials and mechanical
equipment.
</P>
<P>
The boundary between Heilongjiang and Russia is 3045-km long,
constituting 70 percent of the total length of Sino-Russian
border. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971110.0173 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambia Holds 6 for Cocaine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, November 10 (Xinhua) -- Six Zambians have been
arrested for illegal imports and trafficking in about 4.5 kg "of
very high grade" Columbian cocaine with a street value of 3.47
billion Kwacha, or 2.6 million U.S. Dollars, an official said
today.
</P>
<P>
In a telephone interview with Xinhua here, Zambia's Drug
Enforcement Commission (DEC) spokesman Mukutulu Sinyani said that
the suspects, including a young white couple, a businessman, a
computer manager, a clearing clerk and a taxi driver.
</P>
<P>
They were arrested on November 6 at the Lusaka International
Airport by DEC in a joint cooperation with Britain's Customs and
Excise Department.
</P>
<P>
The suspects, whose number is likely to go up as more are
going to be arrested, will appear in court in the capital today,
according to the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
At a news briefing Friday, Sinyani told reporters that the
haul represented a new threat to the country.
</P>
<P>
"The high cocaine straight from Colombia represents a new
threat to our country and therefore the urgent need to intensify
the efforts to stem the tide of this scourge," Sinyani said.
</P>
<P>
He warned that nobody would be safe if this country were to be
engulfed in money and property derived from drug trafficking.
"our pride and integrity both at home and abroad would be
severely dented," said Sinyani.
</P>
<P>
The cocaine was ingeniously compacted in 12 heavy duty 6
voltage torch batteries which were laced with a small battery so
that the internal laser torches could be lit with power from the
dry cell battery embedded in the expertly packed drug.
</P>
<P>
The contraband was meant for both local and export
consumption, according to Sinyani.
</P>
<P>
DEC had been monitoring the contraband at the airport
warehouse where it has been lying for the past two weeks since it
was imported into Zambia before the commission closed in and
pounced on two suspects who later led officers to various places
where the rest were picked up.
</P>
<P>
Earlier reports said that last month, the DEC arrested 136
suspects in connection with drug trafficking in the country.
</P>
</TEXT>
