<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Suzhou Industrial Park Attracts More Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SUZHOU, November 10 (Xinhua) -- The Suzhou Industrial Park,
jointly funded by China and Singapore, began to take on a lively
scene here in Zhejiang Province after three years of construction.
</P>
<P>
David Lim, chairman of China-Singapore Suzhou Industrial Park
Development Co. Ltd., said: "the 15-square-kilometer park has an
irresistible attraction for investors from China and abroad."
</P>
<P>
The park has approved 101 overseas-invested enterprises, each
with an investment exceeding 2.8 million U.S. dollars. The
combined investment has topped 3.38 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Among these enterprises, 77 are engaged in high-tech industries
and 22 have investments from transnational companies listed among
the world's top 500 firms such as Emerson, Lilly, Harris and
Solectron from the United States; Hitachi from Japan; Glaxo
Wellcome from the United Kingdom and Samsung from the Republic of
Korea.
</P>
<P>
So far, 34 overseas-invested industrial enterprises in the park
have become operational.
</P>
<P>
Kenneth S. C. Wong, general manager from Millipore (Suzhou)
Filter Co. Ltd., said: "foreign investors who have opened business
here are confident of the park's infrastructure."
</P>
<P>
Actually, the park's investment in this aspect has been 2.5
times the average amount in other economic development zones in
the country.
</P>
<P>
During the past three years, 4.2 billion yuan (506 million
U.S. dollars) has been pooled for such purposes as transportation,
city greening, postal system, water supply, heating and
electricity.
</P>
<P>
Another 1.5 billion yuan (180 million U.S. dollars) has been
injected into building banks, schools, hospitals, shopping and
hotels.
</P>
<P>
Investors say they are impressed by the efficiency of the
park's administrative commission.
</P>
<P>
It only took 12 months for Samsung Electronics (Suzhou)
Semiconductor Co. Ltd., one of the earliest registered overseas
enterprises in the park, to complete construction and begin
production in its 100,000-square-meter building.
</P>
<P>
Chen Wenxiang, general manager of the Solectron (Suzhou)
Technology Co. Ltd., spoke highly of the park's clear policies on
fees.
</P>
<P>
The park's success can be attributed partly to help from
Singapore. During the last three years, 446 staff members in the
park have been to Singapore for training and a number of
managerial experts from Singapore have given a lot of assistance
to their Chinese colleagues.
</P>
<P>
In the next three years, Suzhou Industrial Park plans to
introduce 2.5 billion U.S. dollars of investment and transfer 550
hectares of land, including 450 hectares for the industrial
sector, 300,000 square meters for commercial purposes and 450,000
square meters for residential housing.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
