<HEADLINE> Shandong Witnesses Comprehensive Agricultural Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, November 10 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shangdong Province
has witnessed comprehensive and sustainable agricultural
development since 1988.
</P>
<P>
The province has allocated 4.08 billion yuan (510 million
U.S. dollars) to transform 1.07 million ha. of medium- to
low-yield farmland, reclaimed 200,000 ha. of wastelands, and
completed the afforestation of an additional 120,000 hectares.
</P>
<P>
The province's total grain output has jumped dramatically to a
record 40 billion kilograms.
</P>
<P>
In addition to promoting the development of agricultural
industrialization, the provincial government has also focused on
supporting pillar industries and establishing production bases for
farm and sideline products.
</P>
<P>
Some 370 million yuan (46.2 million U.S. dollars) has been
invested in establishing organizations to provide technological
support and other services for farmers.
</P>
<P>
The province has fully recognized the important role of
agricultural technology by introducing 623 advanced technological
achievements related to planting and cultivation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
