of 66 million NZ dollars (41 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Telecom shares led the falls, plunging 55 cents to 840 cents
after reaching a record high last Friday. Trading on its shares
accounted for a quarter of the turnover. Also lower were Fletcher
Building, down 17c to 518c, Carter Holt Harvey, slipping 3c to
273c, Air New Zealand, dipping 5c to 245c, and Lion Nathan, easing
5c to 400c.
</P>
