<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, November 10 (Xinhua) -- A U.S. U-2 say plane has
resumed flight over Iraq, but an Iraqi military communique
said it was unable to shot down the plane.
</P>
<P>
The communique said the American spy plane entered Iraqi
airspace at about 8:20 local time (0520 GMT), but it was "out of
range" of the Iraqi anti-aircraft missiles.
</P>
<P>
Washington confirmed the flight of the surveillence plane after
President Clinton declared that the United States will not
tolerate attacks by Iraqi President Saddam Hussein.
</P>
<P>
Baghdad has vowed to fire on the U.S. spy plane overflying Iraq
under the order of the United Nations Special Commission on
dismantling Iraq's weapons of mass destruction.
</P>
<P>
It accused the plane of having run pre-strike missions for the
U.S. to select targets. 
