<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mahathir Dwells on Asia-Europe Partnership </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, November 10 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Prime Minister
Mahathir Mohamad today put stress on forging a partnership between
Asia and Europe for the 21st century to construct a global
prosperity process which will bring prosperity not to a select few
but prosperity for all.
</P>
<P>
Delivering a keynote address at the two-day Global Panel Kuala
Lumpur 1997 which opened here today, Mahathir said the reasons for
Europe and Asia to work together in partnership are:
</P>
<P>
"First because in a shrunken world we are going to be
uncomfortably close neighbors. The Far East is no longer far.
</P>
<P>
"Second because over a broad range of issues, we have and will
increasingly have a common purpose and a shared interest.
</P>
<P>
"Third, there are many challenges which neither Europe nor Asia
can on their own tackle or resolve."
</P>
<P>
In his speech entitled "Asia and Europe: Forging a Partnership
for the 21st Century", Mahathir reminded Asians that there should
be greater partnership with Europe because Europe is strong,
influential and rich.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he reminded Europeans that Southeast Asia, Northeast
Asia and other regions of Asia will become much stronger, much
more influential, much richer in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Acknowledging there are other critical challenges to mankind in
the 21st century, Mahathir spelt out three which he thank need
particular emphasis -- challenges of "building a more peaceful and
more just global commonwealth; ensuring global prosperity; and
ensuring cultural tolerance in a multi-cultural world and ensuring
not only no clash of civilizations but instead, a joyous
celebration of civilizations".
</P>
<P>
On global prosperity in the 21st century, Mahathir said this
can only be achieved through the most massive expansion of trade
in human history and the most massive flows of productive foreign
investment across borders that this planet has ever seen.
</P>
<P>
"Trade and productive investment must be the arteries, the
veins, the tissue, the mussel and the bone of our global
prosperity of the 21st century," he said.
</P>
<P>
On multiple civilization and multiple cultures, the Malaysian
leader said "Cultural and civlizational pluralism will be the
hallmark of the 21st century."
</P>
<P>
Noting that there obviously are universal core human values
which have been accepted, indeed cherished, by societies
throughout history, he said that most of these universal core
human values should continue to be cherished.  
</P>
</TEXT>
