<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India Yet to Decide on Attitude to Western Sahara </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, November 10 (Xinhua) -- India is not in a hurry to
accede to Morocco's demand to withdraw its 1985 recognition of the
Saharawi Arab Democratic Republic (SADR), The Hindustan Times
quoted External Affairs Ministry sources as saying here today.
</P>
<P>
India would wait for the result of a referendum, likely to be
held in the fall of 1998 to decide whether Western Sahara should
become independent from Morocco, before making a decision on the
recognition issue. The 24-year-old civil war, which began in 1976
when Spain ended its colonial rule in Western Sahara, may be over
at last if the referendum is held and its outcome honored by the
two sides.
</P>
<P>
While talking to The Hindustan Times, Moroccan Ambassador
Mohammed Belmahi and SADR Charge D'affaires Mohamed Salem blamed
each other for the long delay in preparing for the referendum.
According to Salem, the Moroccan offensive seeking India's
withdrawal of the recognition of the SADR is linked to the likely
outcome of the referendum.
</P>
<P>
India recognized the SADR in 1985 which pre-dated the United
Nations-sponsored settlement plan, which calls, among others, for
the referendum on self-determination by the people in Western
Sahara.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971110.0201 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indian Inflation Touches Record Low of 3.45 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, November 10 (Xinhua) -- India's annual inflation
plunged to an 11-year low of 3.45 percent for the week ending
October 25, official sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
The annual rate of inflation, calculated on a point-to-point
basis, fell by 0.52 percentage points during the week to 3.45
percent from 3.97 percent in the previous week.
</P>
<P>
The fall in the inflation based on the wholesale price index
during the week is mainly due to relative stability in the prices
of primary food articles compared with a substantial increase in
the prices of the same in the corresponding week last year. The
prices of primary food articles went down by 0.2 percent during
the week compared with a 1.8-percent increase for the same in the
corresponding week last year.
</P>
<P>
Economists believe that the low levels of inflation may be due
to the slackening of demand in the economy, which is quite evident
from the relative stability in the prices of primary articles and
manufactured goods.  
</P>
</TEXT>
