<HEADLINE> Bad Weather Hits Northwestern Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, November 9 (Xinhua) -- High winds and torrential rain
lashed northwestern Italy for the second day today, causing
floods and landslides in Genoa and the surrounding area.
</P>
<P>
Emergency services were on call for much of the day in the big
port, rescuing stranded automobiles, clearing out roads and
pumping out flood water from buildings.
</P>
<P>
Heavy rain also swept Lombardy Region over to the east, with
cars aquaplaning and roads blocked.
</P>
<P>
Civil protection authorities have announced a state of
"pre-alert," saying that if the rain continues to fall as heavily
through the night, river levels might cause concern.
</P>
<P>
Much of the rest of the country also saw some bouts of heavy
rain today, but in the quake-wracked areas of Marche and Umbria,
there were fewer thunderstorms than previous days.
</P>
<P>
