<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ibero-American Summit Ends With Call for Cooperation, Democracy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MARGARITA ISLAND, Venezuela, November 9 (Xinhua) -- The two-day
Ibero-American Summit ended here today with calls for cooperation
among countries and pledges to abide by the ethical value of
democracy.
</P>
<P>
Venezuelan President Rafael Caldera, host of the summit, said
at the closing session that the summit discussed the situation in
Ibero-American countries and confirmed their willingness to abide
by the principle.
</P>
<P>
At the summit, 21 leaders signed the Margarita Statement named
after the tourist resort, 450 kilometers off Venezuela's
northeastern coast.
</P>
<P>
The statement said the Ibero-American countries will show to the
world their new image by strengthening unity and working together
to implement the principles put forward in the statement and serve
the common interests of the people.
</P>
<P>
President Jorge Sampaio of Portugal, the host of the next
year's summit, said the Ibero-American countries have strengthened
their friendship and cooperation through open dialogues.
</P>
<P>
He said the theme of the next summit will be
"challenges of globalization and inter-regional cooperation."
</P>
<P>
Twenty-two leaders from Latin American nations, Spain and
Portugal and the Ecuadoran foreign minister attended the Seventh
Ibero-American Summit which centered on "ethical values of
democracy."
</P>
<P>
In the statement, the leaders said democracy was not only a
means of management, but also a life style of ethical values. They
also pledged to continue improving and strengthening democracy.
</P>
<P>
The statement stressed the importance of cooperation among
countries, saying such cooperation will remain as the basic factor
in the next century in international relations.
</P>
<P>
The leaders of the annual summit also pledged to fight poverty,
corruption and drug trafficking and defend free and fair
elections. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971110.0219 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Official on Electing Deputies to National People's Congress in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 10 (Xinhua) -- The election of deputies of
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) to the Ninth
National People's Congress (NPC) of China should implement the
principle of "one country, two systems", a senior NPC official
said here today.
</P>
<P>
The election should help maintain Hong Kong's prosperity and
stability, give full play to democracy and proceed strictly
according to law, said Cao Zhi, secretary-general of the Standing
Committee of the NPC, at the first session of the Conference for
Electing Deputies of the HKSAR to the Ninth NPC, which opened at
the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center this morning.
</P>
<P>
He said that the election process should be open, just and fair
and that those who support "one country, two systems" and love
the country and Hong Kong would be elected.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the election is an embodiment of the principle
of "one country, two systems" as well as the right of Chinese
citizens among HKSAR residents to participate in the management of
state affairs according to law.
</P>
<P>
Cao told members of the Election Conference that the NPC and
its Standing Committee attach great importance to this election as
it is the first time for Hong Kong to elect deputies to the NPC as
an independent constituency since the Chinese government resumed
the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong on July 1.
</P>
<P>
In March this year, the Fifth Session of the Eighth NPC
formulated the Method for Electing Deputies of the HKSAR to the
Ninth NPC. Not long ago, the 28th Meeting of the Eighth NPC
Standing Committee approved the list of members of the Conference
for Electing Deputies of the HKSAR to the Ninth NPC.
</P>
<P>
Cao, who is entrusted by the NPC Standing Committee to chair
this election, said that the Constitution of the People's Republic
of China, the Basic Law of the HKSAR and the Election Method
constitute the basis for this election.
</P>
<P>
The NPC, China's supreme organ of state power, and its
permanent body, the NPC Standing Committee, exercise the
legislative power of the state, make decisions on important
national affairs, supervise the work of the State Council, the
Central Military Commission, the Supreme People's Court and the
Supreme People's Procuratorate, and elect and decide on
functionaries of state organs.
</P>
<P>
"The system of the people's congress is the fundamental
political system practiced in China," Cao said.
</P>
<P>
Deputies to the NPC are members of the supreme organ of state
power, and they participate in exercising state power according to
the functions and powers endowed to the NPC by the Constitution
and the law. When the NPC is in session, the deputies attend
meetings, review motions and reports on the agenda of the session,
submit motions and raise opinions and suggestions according to
law, and take part in various elections. When the NPC is not in
session, the deputies participate in activities organized by the
NPC Standing Committee and associate with ordinary citizens and
heed their opinions and raise proposals, opinions and criticisms
to the NPC Standing Committee with regard to the work in various
fields.
</P>
<P>
According to the principle of "one country, two systems" and
provisions in the Basic Law of the HKSAR, the HKSAR does not
practice the system of the people's congress, Cao said.
</P>
<P>
Chinese citizens among HKSAR residents elect according to law
deputies to the NPC to participate in the work of the supreme
organ of state power.
</P>
<P>
In addition to exercising the above-mentioned functions and
powers according to law, HKSAR deputies to the NPC are entitled to
submitting motions on amending the Basic Law of the HKSAR and
joining the committee for electing the Chief Executive and the
Legislative Council of the HKSAR in accordance with the Basic Law.
</P>
<P>
Cao said that the HKSAR deputies to the NPC are not entitled to
supervising the HKSAR government, and should neither interfere in
the work of the HKSAR government nor interfere in the affairs
which are within the framework of the high degree of autonomy of
the HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
According to the Election Method adopted at the Fifth Session
of the Eighth NPC, Chinese citizens among HKSAR residents at age
18 or above can apply for the election of deputies to the Ninth
NPC.
</P>
<P>
The applicants will run as individual candidates and should not
represent any political parties or organizations, Cao said.
</P>
<P>
The elected deputies of the HKSAR to the NPC, as members of the
supreme organ of state power, should love the country and love
Hong Kong, support the principle of "one country, two systems",
support and abide by the Constitution of the PRC and the Basic Law
and laws of the HKSAR, and perform the duties of the deputies in
line with the procedural rules of the NPC and other legal
provisions, he added.
</P>
<P>
Cao expressed the hope that, in the election, both members of
the Election Conference and the applicants will put to good use
their rights and obligations according to law and in the spirit of
being responsible for the country and for Hong Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
