<HEADLINE> New Thai Government to Focus on Foreign Affairs, Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, November 10 (Xinhua) -- Foreign affairs and trade will
be the focus of the new Thai government in a bid to bring about a
speedy economic recovery and restore much-needed confidence of
foreign investors, according to local press today.
</P>
<P>
Democrat Party leader Chuan Leekpai was appointed new prime
minister of Thailand Sunday. According to Democrat Party
Secretary-General Sanan Kachornprasart, Chuan Leekpai's new
cabinet line-up will be completed on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Overall policy objective will be geared toward exercising
leadership on issues that will advance Thailand's economic and
strategic interests such as finance cooperation, market
liberalization, exports and investment, and the transfer of
technology and tourism, Democrat Party officials were quoted as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Chuan Leekpai is likely to present his government's policy in
parliament when it convenes an extraordinary session soon.
</P>
<P>
The policies and strategies set out by the new Chuan Leekpai
government will represent change and continuity that give priority
to forging closer ties with neighboring countries, both in
bilateral and multilateral frameworks such as ASEAN, the
Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) forum and the Asia-Europe
meeting.
</P>
<P>
The new Thai government will give special emphasis to the
upcoming APEC meeting, the informal ASEAN summit in December in
Kuala Lumpur and the Asia-Europe meeting in London in April.
</P>
<P>
Chuan Leekpai will head the Thai delegation to the fifth
Asia-Pacific Economic Leaders Meeting in Vancouver from November
22 to 26.
</P>
<P>
Chuan Leekpai is scheduled to leave Bangkok next Saturday for
Vancouver, via Hong Kong, to open a new Thai consular office.
</P>
<P>
Chuan Leekpai's government will continue to promote Thailand as
a regional hub for finance and telecommunication, and the
development of regional and sub-regional economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Emphasis will also be given to establishing new regional
security measures to ensure peace and prosperity through a
consultative and confidence-building mechanism under the ASEAN
regional forum.  
</P>
