<HEADLINE> Economic Growth Registered in Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, November 10 (Xinhua) -- A number of economic sectors
ranging from development zones to pillar industries and to
overseas-funded businesses have contributed to rapid growth in
Tianjin, a northern China coastal city.
</P>
<P>
The local Binhai New Area leads all local economic sectors in
bringing in 43 percent of the growth, up from 29 percent three
years ago.
</P>
<P>
High-tech industries such as metallurgy, chemicals,
electronics, information and bio-engineering have become
established in the zone.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to the transformation of these large and medium-size
state enterprises, the city's industrial output has increased by
57 percent.
</P>
<P>
Overseas-funded enterprises have become a major resource for
the local economy, bringing in nearly 46 percent of local
growth. More than three-fifths of local exports was attributed to
foreign-funded businesses during the first half of 1997.
</P>
<P>
The city has invested more than 56 billion yuan in recent years
in the development of service sector industries such as commerce,
trade, finance, transportation, telecommunications, information,
consulting, tourism, stock exchange and real estate.
</P>
<P>
The booming services industry now accounts for 42 percent of
the local gross domestic production, which is expected to rise 1.2
percentage points a year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
