<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Spaniard Alonso Wins Santiago Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, November 9 (Xinhua) -- Spain's Julian Alonso toppled
top seed Marcelo Rios of Chile 6-2, 6-1 to win the Santiago Open
men's tennis tournament here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Alonso, ranked 45th in the world and seeded fourth in the
tournament, denied Rios both a victory at home and a chance to
qualify for next week's Masters Tournament in Hanover.
</P>
<P>
This was the first win for the 20-year-old Spaniard as "this is
the first year that I have played big tournaments."
</P>
<P>
Rios, who has lost in the final here three years in a row,
hardly displayed any of his talents during the final.
</P>
<P>
In the first set both played erratically, but the Spaniard
committed less errors. Alonso broke Rios' service in the fourth
and the eighth games to take the set 6-2.
</P>
<P>
The second set was almost a replay of the first, except that
Alonso made less mistakes. He broke Rios' service in the second
and the fourth games to seal the competition in 47 minutes.
</P>
</TEXT>
