<HEADLINE> Vietnamese City Links Trade Through the Taiwan Strait </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, November 10 (Xinhua) -- Vietnamese Haiphong city has
become a new transit port for China's mainland exports to Taiwan,
thanks to favorable policies of the Vietnamese government.
</P>
<P>
Between July and October, 300 tons of goods, mainly fresh
onions and Chinese-onion-flavored pies, were shipped to Taiwan via
coastal Haiphong, which forms a geographic tirangle between
China's Guangxi Zhaung Autonomous Region, Taiwan and itself.
</P>
<P>
Exports of taro, sweet-potato powder, wooden hangers and toys
are also expected to make destination in Taiwan soon, according to
official sources.
</P>
<P>
Cargo ships are making regular runs between Haiphong and
Taiwan. Since September 26, special treatment has been offered at
Vietnamese customs bordering on southern China's Guangxi.  
</P>
</TEXT>
