<HEADLINE> China's Fast-Food Industry Targets a New High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 10 (Xinhua) -- China's fast-food industry is
growing by leaps and bounds, with the number of outlets up by
five percent annually, according to the Ministry of Internal
Trade.
</P>
<P>
Of the newly-added outlets, the ministry said, 30 percent will
be modern restaurants and chain stores.
</P>
<P>
Sales from the fast-food industry is expected to account for 25
percent of the country's catering sector by 2000.
</P>
<P>
China's fast-food services have been expanding rapidly with
400,000 outlets nationwide, including 800 specialized fast-food
companies and 4,000 fast-food chain stores.
</P>
<P>
The industry reported 40 billion yuan (4.8 billion
U.S. dollars) in 1996 turnover, accounting for 20 percent of the
country's catering sector.
</P>
<P>
The ministry urged relevant departments in localities to devote
more efforts in introducing modern management methods in
developing Chinese-flavor fast-food restaurants to satisfy the
increasing domestic demand as well as to participate in the fierce
competition in international markets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
