<HEADLINE> Costa Rica Draws Mexico 3-3 in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, November 9 (Xinhua) -- Costa Rica rallied twice
from two-goal deficits to draw Mexico 3-3 here on Sunday in a
CONCACAF World Cup qualifier.
</P>
<P>
Mexico surged to a 2-0 lead on goals through Paulo Chavez in
the opening minute and Benjamin Galindo three minutes before
halftime.
</P>
<P>
Carlos Hermosillo netted the third goal in the 68th minute,
giving Mexico a 3-1 lead after Hernan Medford scored in the 54th
minute for Costa Rica.
</P>
<P>
But Costa Rica managed for a 3-3 tie as Jafet Soto pulled one
more back in the 71st and Paulo Wahchope scored with less than
three minutes left.
</P>
<P>
The draw left Costa Rica with a 2-3-4 record and nine points,
four fewer than Jamaica with one match remaining in the battle for
the third and final place for the 1998 World Cup Finals from
CONCACAF.
</P>
<P>
Jamaica drew 2-2 with El Salvador in San Salvador, leaving the
two sides in the battle for the final berth.
</P>
<P>
The United States clinched its place with a 3-0 victory over
Canada, also on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Mexico, which already had clinched its place in the 32-team
finals, improved to 4-5-0 and remained atop the standings. 
</P>
