<HEADLINE> Shanghai Shipping Exchange Makes Good Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, November 10 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai Shipping Exchange,
the country's first state-class shipping trading center, has
turned out a transaction volume of more than 53.1 billion yuan in
the first 10 months since it was inaugurated.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Shipping Exchange was set up last November. By
September of 1997, it had handled 3.8 million tons of goods,
clinching deals totalling 53.141 billion yuan, an average monthly
increase of 25 percent.
</P>
<P>
At present, the goods reported at the customs by the Shanghai
Shipping Exchange have been shippped to more than 20 countries and
regions, including the Republic of Korea, Israel and Japan. 
</P>
