visit to China as guest of his Chinese counterpart Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
This is Yeltsin's third state visit to China. The two heads of
state are expected to hold their fifth summit Monday.
 (China-Russia-Arrival)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BANGKOK -- Thailand's newly-appointed prime minister, Chuan
Leekpai, said here Sunday that the restoration of investors'
confidence and the stabilization of the country's currency, the
baht, are the priority of his government.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference held here after his appointment
by King Bhumibul Adulyadej, Chuan said he will do his best to
solve the problems facing the country and called on the people to
cooperate and help the government solve the country's problems.
(Thailand-Chuan-Prime Minister)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NEW YORK -- The value of worldwide company mergers has reached
a record high of 760 billion U.S. dollars so far this year, the
New York Times reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The dollar value of mergers grew each year since 1993 when it
stood at only over 200 billion dollars, a U.S. consulting firm
Securities Data Corporation was quoted by the Times as
saying. (Company-Merger) 
</P>
