<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South Korea Beats UAE 3-1 in World Cup Tie </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, November 9 (Xinhua) -- Kim Do-Hoon scored twice to
lead South Korea's 3-1 victory over the United Arab Emirates in a
World Cup Asian group B qualifier here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
With the South Koreans already into next year's finals in
France and UAE out of run for second place, which the Japanese
secured, the game was only a formality.
</P>
<P>
Lee Sang-Yoon opened the scoring for South Korea in the 11th
minute with Kim Do-Hoon making it 2-0 in the 42nd for a
comfortable half-time advantage.
</P>
<P>
The Emirates launched several attacks in the second half, and
their star striker Zuhair Bakhit pulled one goal back in the 52nd
minute, tapping the ball in after a defensive lapse.
</P>
<P>
However, the technically superior South Koreans regained their
two-goal cushion when Kim Do-Hoon fired his second goal in the
67th minute.
</P>
<P>
Only the two Asian group winners automatically qualify for the
finals.
</P>
<P>
The runners-up of the two groups will meet to decide a third
Asian berth. Japan will now go to Malaysia to meet Asian Group
A's runner-up in a crucial playoff on November 16.
</P>
<P>
Japan's opponent will be decided next week from among Iran,
Saudi Arabia and Qatar. 
</P>
</TEXT>
