<HEADLINE> Bjorkman Wins Stockholm Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, November 9 (Xinhua) -- Jonas Bjorkman rallied from
3-6 and 2-4 down to beat Jan Siemerink in four sets on Sunday and
win the Stockholm Open tennis tournament for the first time.
</P>
<P>
The Swede took two hours and 10 minutes before winning 3-6, 7-6
(7-2), 6-2, 6-4 for his 67th match victory of the year.
</P>
<P>
Bjorkman pocketed 112,000 dollars for his third ATP Tour
singles title of the year. His earlier victories came at Auckland
and Indianapolis.
</P>
<P>
Bjorkman's victory enabled Sweden to claim the title for the
third straight year. Thomas Enqvist won in 1995 and 1996.
</P>
<P>
The 25-year-old Swede, who will play in the ATP Tour World
Championship in Germany starting Tuesday, will remain No. 4 in the
men's rankings.
</P>
<P>
Only three other Swedes, Bjorn Borg, Mats Wilander and Stefan
Edberg have been ranked higher than Bjorkman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
