<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kafelnikov Takes Kremlin Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, November 9 (Xinhua) -- Russian tennis star Yevgeny
Kafelnikov ousted Petr Korda of the Czech Republic 7-6 (7-2), 6-4,
to take the Kremlin Cup Sunday and qualify for this week's ATP
Tour Championship.
</P>
<P>
Kafelnikov, last year's runner-up, broke Korda's serve in the
second game, but second-seeded Korda immediately broke back. The
only other break came with Korda serving in the third game of the
second set.
</P>
<P>
Kafelnikov, who rose to seventh in the ATP Tour rankings, had
played Korda twice before this year, beating him both times.
</P>
<P>
Korda, who was ranked 15th before the match, has yet to win a
tournament this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
