<HEADLINE> South Korea's Relay Title Stripped </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, November 9 (Xinhua) -- South Korea was stripped of
its title in the men's 5,000 meters relay because of obstruction
at the short track speed skating Olympic qualifying competition in
the Hague of the Netherlands on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Olympic champion Italy stepped in as winner and Japan was
promoted to second place with China third.
</P>
<P>
The disqualification however, did not affect South Korea's
participation in the Nagano Olympic Games because it had already
secured its spot as one of eight teams to reach the semi-finals.
</P>
<P>
The disqualification ruined what would otherwise have been a
perfect day for the South Koreans who earlier had won the women's
3,000 meters in a time of 4:19.958. China was second and Canada
third. 
</P>
</TEXT>
