<HEADLINE> Jamaica, Salvador Draw 2-2 in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, November 9 (Xinhua) -- Jamaica denied El
Salvador's home turf advantage to draw its rival 2-2 in a World
Cup soccer qualifier.
</P>
<P>
The draw left Jamaica three points ahead of Salvador in the
fight for the last of three berths for the 1998 finals from
CONCACAF.
</P>
<P>
Mexico clinched its place last week and the United States
assured itself of another with a 3-0 victory over Canada on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Jamaica can clinch the final berth with a draw next Sunday at
home against Mexico or if El Salvador fails to beat the United
States in Foxboro, Massachusetts.
</P>
<P>
If Mexico and Salvador both win, Salvador would qualify over
Jamaica on a better goal differential. 
</P>
</TEXT>
