<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australians Take Top Three in Yachting Opening Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 9 (Xinhua) -- Australians took the top
three places in the opening race of the 1997 Oriental Overseas
Container Line Ltd. (OOCL) Etchells World Yachting Championships
here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Australia's Noel Drennan led all the way to take the opening
race. His fellow countryman, 1996 Olympic bronze-medalist and
two-time Etchells world champion Colin Beashel was second and
America's Cup legend John Bertrand, also from Australia, was
third. Hong Kong's Mark Thornburrow finished fourth.
</P>
<P>
Sailing in 16 knots of wind, Drennan rounded the marks first
throughout the race. Bertrand was second around each mark until
the last leg when Beashel was able to pull ahead of him to steal
the second place. Denmark's two-time Olympic champion Poul-Richard
Hoj-Jensen fell from third to fifth at the finish line.
</P>
<P>
The sailors are allowed to throw one out of the six races of
the world championships.
</P>
<P>
Thirty boats and 91 sailors from six countries and regions are
competing in the championships.
</P>
<P>
The eight-day OOCL World Championships is the last leg of the
OOCL World Series in which skippers are competing for the OOCL
World Series Trophy based on their accumulated points over the
three-year, four-regatta series. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
